for those interested in NCR news:
DAYTON, Ohio, Oct. 9 /PRNewswire/ -- In a move to bring banking
convenience to Kmart customers, NCR Corporation (NYSE: NCR) and Kmart
announced today that they will install more than 1,100 ATMs in Kmart
stores across the United States. NCR and Kmart also will partner with
several banks nationwide to provide banking services throughout Kmart's
retail network.

"Consumers now place greater emphasis on convenience than ever before,"
said Andy Orent, vice president, self service, NCR. "In the last five
years, there has been a 74 percent growth in ATMs outside the
traditional bank branch -- in locations such as convenience stores, gas
stations and retail stores like Kmart. NCR's long-standing expertise
in both the financial and retail sectors, enables us to provide
world-class quality ATMs to help meet the needs of customers."

NCR will install its ATMs in the highest-volume Kmart stores in every
state in the continental United States. In addition to the ATMs, NCR
Worldwide Customer Services will provide implementation and support
solutions that includes site audit, wiring and daily support services.
The NCR cash dispensers will deliver an added service to Kmart
customers and enhance the overall convenience of shopping in Kmart
stores.

"NCR brings world-class ATMs to Kmart, enabling our consumers to access
cash whenever they need it most," said Paul Hueber, senior vice
president, store operations, Kmart. "NCR has distinct capabilities and
understanding of the retail market, making them the best ATM provider
for our stores."

Last year, the number of ATMs installed in non-bank locations more than
doubled to almost 22,000 -- 10,000 more than the number of ATMs placed
in traditional bank locations. According to Orent, this explosion is
driven by consumer demand for fast, convenient access to cash.

Kmart Corporation (NYSE: KM) common stock is listed on the New York,
Pacific and Chicago Stock Exchanges. Kmart Corporation serves America
with 2,122 Kmart, Big Kmart and Super Kmart stores. In addition to
serving all 50 states, Kmart operations extend to Puerto Rico, the U.S.
Virgin Islands, and Guam.

NCR's Financial Systems Group is an industry leader in three primary
areas: financial delivery systems including self-service, relationship
banking data warehousing solutions and image and payment systems.
These solutions allow financial institutions to reach customers more
effectively and to develop more tightly linked relationships through
self-service, traditional bank branches, call centers and home banking
channels. NCR Corporation designs, develops, markets and services
information technology products, services, systems and solutions
worldwide. NCR is located on the World Wide Web at www.ncr.com .
SOURCE NCR Corporation
