under value. They hold some good patents and they aren't afraid to protect
them. Looks like potential in many areas. Take over is unlikely as the B shares
are non-trading shares held by insiders and have 10x voting power of A common,
otherwise equal. All this does is insure that current management makes the
decisions.

I like it more now than when I first looked at it.

