From:Paul Senior

Chris Pedicini: re AG and NH. I look at it differently. What is the purpose of
the investment in these ag co's? If these stocks popped out on somebody's
screen because of low pe or psr, I say that the psr's and p/book and pe
(figures for AG anyway) are not low compared to past years. The industry has
been cylical - maybe now the bet is that with China & other markets, that's no
longer true. My opinion is that there's not much room for improvement in the
ratio's, and there's some risk that the current valuations reflect a cyclical
high. From the very little I know, it seems that there is a number of strong
competitors - sort of like with auto manufacturers. I'd pass on both these co's
at current prices unless I really knew the industry. And if I had to spend the
time to really learn the industry, I wouldn't spend my time on this industry
unless I was already ancillarily involved (like being a farmer). I think the
time to buy these companies is when they are in the "losing money" part of the
cycle. JMO .... and I've been plenty wrong before (I looked at Navistar and
figured it to be in the same category-- and the stock's gone up 3x)
